Package: ibus-ethiopic
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, ibus (>= 1.5)
Description: IBus engine for Ethiopic input
 A two-layer Ethiopic input method: a platform-independent C++ core
 library (libethio) and a thin IBus engine wrapper. Supports all
 Ethiopic-script languages (Amharic, Tigrinya, Oromo, Guragigna, etc.)
 via SERA transliteration with auto-commit, prefix disambiguation,
 word suggestions, and labiovelar forms.

Package: libethio-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: ibus-ethiopic (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Development files for libethio
 Headers and static library for developing applications or input method
 wrappers (Windows TSF, macOS IMKit, Android, iOS) using the libethio
 trie-based Ethiopic input engine.
